Female
(
Figs. 1
, 
5
, 
9, 11
). Description: 
Measurements:
Approximate body length: 26.0; head width: 7.7; thorax width: 9.7; forewing length: 19.0; UID: 3.3; LID: 3.8; mandible length: 3.6; mandible basal width: 1.8; F1 length: 1.9; F2 length: 0.4; F3 length: 0.5. 
Coloration:
Orange brown, except frons reddish brown (
Fig. 1
). Upper paraocular area and mesoscutum dark brown (
Fig. 1
). Vertex dark brown to black (
Fig. 1
). Lower paraocular area and tegula yellowish brown (
Figs. 1
, 
5
). Metasoma dark brown (
Fig. 5
). Wing membrane and veins dark brown (
Fig. 5
) with violaceous iridescence. 
Sculpture:
Clypeus finely areolate, less evident on disc, with thick and dense punctures on laterosuperior margin, finer towards lower edge (di<ds). Labrum with coarse, not very dense and uniform punctures (di<ds), with well-defined areolate and impunctate surface on upper margin. T1 with fine and dense punctures (di<ds). T2 and T3 with similar punctures of T1 but denser (di≈ds). T4–T6 with slightly coarser and scattered punctures (di>ds). 
Pubescence:
Head with dark brown to black hairs (
Fig. 1
). Labrum with mostly simple, downwardly directed hairs (
Fig. 1
). Surface below wings and legs mostly with dark brown pilosity, except middle femur with light brown hairs (
Fig. 5
). Pronotum and propodeum with brown yellowish pilosity. Mesepisternum with orange brown hairs laterally, brown ventrally. T1 with dark brown plumose hairs (
Fig. 5
). T2 and T3 with very dense pubescence (
Fig. 5
). T4 and T5 with similar pilosity to preceding terga, with some simple hairs intermixed. Prepygidial and pygidial fimbriae with dark brown hairs (
Fig. 11
). 
Structures:
Flabellum elliptical with slightly narrow anterior margin. Mandible strongly curved apically (
Fig. 1
). Acetabular carina reaching the base of third tooth. Trimal angle well-developed, acute. Maxillary palpus with four palpomeres (2nd>3rd>1st≈4th). Clypeus uniformly convex (lateral view). Labrum relatively triangular. Vertex above upper interocular tangent (
Fig. 1
). Inner orbits of compound eyes slightly converging upwards (
Fig. 1
). Fore elaiospathe with anterior secondary comb formed by five giant apically curved hairs. Mesoscutellum with two not well-developed protuberances. Axilla raised and glabrous. Primary pygidial plate with truncate apex (
Fig. 11
); secondary plate well-developed, with acute apex (
Fig. 11
). Pretarsal claws with preapical tooth, except on hind leg.

Inner orbits of compound eyes converging upwards (
Fig. 2
). Mesoscutellum with two not well-developed protuberances. Axilla raised and glabrous. Primary pygidial plate with bilobed apex.
